# Deck quality checklist (pre-delivery)

Apply when handing off a built or optimized decklist.

## Format

- [ ] **100 cards** total (1 commander + 99 mainboard)
- [ ] **Singleton** (except basic lands)
- [ ] **Color identity** — every mainboard card legal for commander
- [ ] **Banlist** — none from `data/Banlist.txt`
- [ ] All card names resolve in `cards.db` (no invented names)

## Bracket 3

- [ ] Game Changers ≤ 3
- [ ] Extra-turn cards ≤ 3
- [ ] No mass land destruction flagged by analyzer
- [ ] No banned two-card combo wins before turn 6
- [ ] Do **not** reject fast mana (Sol Ring, Vault, Tomb, Mox Opal) as “illegal for Bracket 3” — see `docs/bracket3-official-rules.md`

## Template (bracket3)

- [ ] Critical categories not `below` min (especially ramp, draw, removal, lands)
- [ ] No excessive `above` max without reason
- [ ] `lintReport.ok` or hard issues explained

## Synergy (when strategy chosen)

- [ ] **`synergyScore`** ≥ 60 when `preferredStrategy` set (or user accepts lower with rationale)
- [ ] No obvious off-theme cards unless user requested hybrid
- [ ] One synergy only — no mixed archetypes

## Mana / curve (soft)

- [ ] Average CMC reasonable for strategy (often ≤ 3.2 for midrange)
- [ ] Enough early ramp / rocks for game plan

## MCP verification

Run **`analyze_deck`** with `preferredStrategy` and confirm output matches this checklist before final decklist.
